						<summary>

						<p>Slab lying near the ruined temple of Śiva.</p>						

						<p>Achyutarāya.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1460 (expired), Viḷambi, Āshāḍha,</hi> corresponding to 1538 A.D., July.</p>						

						<p>Damaged and wornout. It seems to register gift of the village Chiḍipirāḷḷadinne in Chāmgalamaṟi-sīma for the worship and offerings to a local god (name and other details are lost).</p>						

						</summary>
